# MongoDB Local Setup Guide (Windows)

This guide explains how to set up a local MongoDB server and restore a MongoDB backup for development.

---

# Prerequisites

Install the following:

## 1. MongoDB Community Server

Purpose:
- Runs the local MongoDB database.
- Default port: 27017

Download:
https://www.mongodb.com/try/download/community

Install:
- Community Edition
- Windows MSI
- Complete Installation
- Install as Windows Service (Recommended)

Verify:

```bash
mongod --version
```

---

## 2. MongoDB Database Tools

Purpose:
- mongodump
- mongorestore
- bsondump

Download:
https://www.mongodb.com/try/download/database-tools

Verify:

```bash
mongodump --version
mongorestore --version
```

---

## 3. MongoDB Compass (Optional)

Purpose:
- GUI for viewing databases

Download:
https://www.mongodb.com/products/tools/compass

Connect:

```
mongodb://localhost:27017
```

---

# Local MongoDB

Default connection string

```text
mongodb://localhost:27017
```

---

# Backup Database From Remote Server

Example:

```bash
mongodump --uri="YOUR_MONGODB_CONNECTION_STRING" --out="D:\MongoBackup"
```

Example output:

```
MongoBackup/
├── Copilot/
├── Admin_Central/
├── admin/
└── node-boilerplate/
```

---

# Restore Backup Into Local MongoDB

Restore all databases:

```bash
mongorestore --drop "D:\MongoBackup"
```

Restore only one database:

```bash
mongorestore --drop --db Copilot "D:\MongoBackup\Copilot"
```

---

# Verify

Open Compass

Connect

```
mongodb://localhost:27017
```

You should see databases like:

```
Copilot
Admin_Central
node-boilerplate
```

---

# Useful Commands

Check MongoDB Server

```bash
mongod --version
```

Check Database Tools

```bash
mongodump --version
mongorestore --version
```

Check MongoDB Service

```bash
sc query MongoDB
```

Start MongoDB Service

```bash
net start MongoDB
```

Stop MongoDB Service

```bash
net stop MongoDB
```

